  ' SENSING
  ' ============================================================

  class Sensing {
    +getName(): String
    +getActuation(): Actuation
    +getSensor(): Sensor
    +getActuationEventArchetype(): EventArchetype
    +getFeedbackEventArchetype(): EventArchetype
    +getControlFeedbackReceptor(): Receptor
  }

  note top of Sensing
    A sensing links actuation execution to feedback reception, enabling
    homeostatic loops on actuations.

    **Systemic Semantics**:
    - Sensing observes the event emitted by the actuator and forwards feedback
      to a control feedback receptor.

    **Auto Definition Rules**:
    - A Sensing (and its Sensor) MUST be auto-defined only if the
      declaring Control defines a feedback receptor.
    - The sensor MUST have a receptor bound to the actuator effector's
      actuation event archetype.
    - The sensor MUST have an effector bound to the feedback receptor's event
      archetype.

    **Validation Rules**:
    - The feedback event archetype MUST be a subtype of
      ActuationFeedbackEventSchema.

    **Incoherences / Drifts**:
    - Sensing defined without a control feedback receptor.
    - Sensor mechanism missing receptor/effector bindings to actuation/feedback
      event archetypes.
  end note

